<p>CONGRATULATIONS ! You have setup a mail server (well almost)</p>
<p>Now that the server is running, you can access https://${MAILCOW_HOSTNAME} with the default credentials <code>admin</code> + password <code>moohoo</code> and start setting up domains and email addresses.</p>
<p>Mailcow has a great <a href="https://docs.mailcow.email/post_installation/firststeps-ssl/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">help site</a> which will walk you through most of the settings that I have not covered.</p>
<h2 id="end" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#end" class="header-mark" aria-label="Header mark for 'End'"></a>End</h2><p>I hope that with this short post, you can see that it&rsquo;s not actually hard to setup a mailserver. What is hard is keeping of spam lists and fighting incoming spam, but for personal use and with the help of Mailcow you should be fine.</p>
<p>Another thing you should not forget is &hellip; BACKUPS.</p>
<p>If you host your main email on this server, you should back it up regularly.</p>
